# deploy.conf — site-local overrides for scripts/deploy.sh
#
# Copy to scripts/deploy.conf (gitignored) or to
# ~/.config/palace-daemon/deploy.conf and edit. Every value is optional;
# unset ones fall back to the documented defaults in deploy.sh. This file is
# sourced as bash, so quote values and don't add side effects.

# ssh target running the daemon (required unless PALACE_DAEMON_URL is set).
# PALACE_HOST="familiar"

# Base URL to poll for /health. Defaults to http://${PALACE_HOST}:8085.
# PALACE_DAEMON_URL="http://familiar:8085"

# x-api-key for the post-deploy route smoke test. Leave unset for an
# auth-less daemon. Prefer sourcing from a secret store over hardcoding.
# PALACE_API_KEY="..."

# Repo path on the deploy host. Defaults to the local git toplevel, which is
# correct for Syncthing/rsync mirrors that preserve the path.
# PALACE_REMOTE_DIR="/home/jp/Projects/palace-daemon"

# How the service is restarted on the host (run via ssh).
# PALACE_RESTART_CMD="sudo systemctl restart palace-daemon"

# For mirror-based deploys (Syncthing/rsync) where the host is NOT a git
# remote: seconds to wait for the mirror to catch up after the push. With a
# real git remote on the host, leave at 0 (SHAs are compared directly).
# PALACE_SYNC_GRACE=3

# Seconds to wait for /health after the restart.
# PALACE_HEALTH_TIMEOUT=30

# Optional command run on the host (login shell) before the restart. JP uses
# this to reset an out-of-tree mempalace clone's git state, since Syncthing
# excludes .git so the working tree is current but HEAD drifts:
# PALACE_PRE_RESTART_HOOK="cd /home/jp/Projects/memorypalace && git fetch origin --quiet && git reset --hard origin/main --quiet"
